      "writtenOn": "2026-06-24T07:38:22Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I\u0027m actually a bit surprised this works, for a different reason: I thought we\u0027d need to do `cue export ./ver/ver.cue` otherwise it would be interpreted as an absolute path. As `cue help inputs` says:\n\n\u003e An import path\n\u003e that begins with a \".\" or \"..\" element is a relative import path,\n\u003e is interpreted as a file system path, and denotes the\n\u003e package instance in that directory.\n\nBut that\u0027s another issue and behaviour that we possibly can\u0027t change now anyway.",
      "revId": "1585b4b8af300b0cd370e66840ae41115cf3aa9d",
      "serverId": "d5d70762-12d0-45a1-890d-524b12d3f735"
    },
    {
      "unresolved": false,
      "key": {
        "uuid": "81e35051_2299178b",
        "filename": "cmd/cue/cmd/testdata/script/load_module_context.txtar",
        "patchSetId": 1
      },
      "lineNbr": 22,
      "author": {
        "id": 1017720
      },
      "writtenOn": "2026-06-24T09:11:47Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Remember that filetypes understands that any argument ending in `.cue` is a file, and NOT an import path, so the \"starts with a dot\" rule does not apply.\n\nOtherwise `cue export foo.cue` would never work, and you\u0027d have to do `cue export ./foo.cue`, which is a bit silly. We have the same behavior as Go in this respect, which I think is reasonable and user-friendly.\n\nSo IMO nothing to fix here, other than a clarification in the `cue help inputs` wording if you want to send a patch.",
      "parentUuid": "9ea982fd_f3d19895",
      "revId": "1585b4b8af300b0cd370e66840ae41115cf3aa9d",
      "serverId": "d5d70762-12d0-45a1-890d-524b12d3f735"
    },
